burlap.oomdp.legacy

Class StateYAMLParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.oomdp.legacy.StateYAMLParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StateParser

    public class StateYAMLParser
extends java.lang.Object
implements StateParser
    A StateParser class that uses the YAML file format and can can convert states to YAML strings (and back from them) for any possible input domain. Use of this class requries the SnakeYaml java library.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan

    • Constructor Detail

      • StateYAMLParser

        public StateYAMLParser(Domain domain)
        Initializes with a a given domain object. The domain object is used for converting from strings to states. Specifically, the object instances will be assigned to the object class in the domain object with the given name in the state string.
        Parameters:
        domain - the domain object to which state objects will be associated.
